  "tutorial": "## Stripe API Key Setup\n\n### Getting Your Stripe API Key\n\n1. Go to [Stripe Dashboard](https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys)\n2. Copy your **Secret Key** (starts with `sk_test_` for test mode or `sk_live_` for live mode)\n\n### Test vs Live Mode\n\n- **Test mode** (`sk_test_*`): Use for development and testing\n- **Live mode** (`sk_live_*`): Use for production with real payments\n\n### Required Permissions\n\nThe API key provides full access to your Stripe account. For restricted access:\n1. Go to **Developers > API keys > Restricted keys**\n2. Create a key with only the permissions you need\n\n### Security Best Practices\n\n- Never expose your secret key in client-side code\n- Use test mode keys during development\n- Rotate keys periodically\n- Use restricted keys when possible",
